    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-10-03T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-10-03T11:00:00-05:00" n="515"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d515">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">894.00/10–345: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Acting Political Adviser in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Atcheson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-10-03T11:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 3, 1945—11 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>13. Please inform the Department what action has been taken regarding the release
                    of Japanese political prisoners. There are reports in America that many have not
                    been liberated.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
